  "text": "In studies including higher proportions of individuals with insulin resistance (obesity, metabolic syndrome, and type 2 diabetes), the discordance between LDL-C and total and small LDL particles increases. After multivariate adjustment, including major CHD risk factors, TG, and HDL-C, LDL particles are associated with a 2-fold higher risk of atherosclerosis and CVD events (reviewed in Rosenson et al. [CITATION_1] ).",
